GENRAG
GENRAG is an organization focused on revolutionizing access to internal knowledge using artificial intelligence, specifically by implementing Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems.<SEP>GENRAG is an organization providing a platform for creating and deploying custom intelligent assistants, without requiring technical expertise. It offers a robust API and intuitive interface, facilitating integration and use.

Quentin Bolloré
Quentin Bolloré is a Fullstack Developer at PoC Innovation with experience in deploying numerous cloud-based applications. At GenRAG, he is responsible for developing the platform and deployment infrastructure for RAG solutions.<SEP>Quentin Bolloré is an individual associated with GENRAG, likely involved in its development and operations.<SEP>Quentin Bolloré is a full-stack developer involved with GenRAG, integrating the latest technological advancements and managing deployment infrastructure.

Valentin Peron
Valentin Peron is an AI R&D Developer at PoC Innovation and a specialist in Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and LLM. He has designed a multimodal chatbot, developed a GPT model from scratch, and implemented RAG solutions for enterprises at GenRAG.<SEP>Valentin Peron is an individual associated with GENRAG, contributing to its initiatives and development.<SEP>Valentin Peron is an AI expert at PoC Innovation, contributing his expertise to GenRAG's technological advancements and deployment infrastructure.

ChatGPT
ChatGPT refers to an AI technology that provides general information, but is noted for not being tailored for specific enterprise needs and lacks real-time adaptability.

RAG
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a system used by GenRAG to combine information retrieval and text generation, providing accurate, verified responses.<SEP>Retrieval-Augmented Generation, or RAG, is a system combining information retrieval and text generation to provide accurate and sourced responses adaptable to enterprise environments.

Enterprise A
Enterprise A is an example of a small-to-medium enterprise with moderate usage of GENRAG's RAG solution.

Enterprise B
Enterprise B represents a larger enterprise with advanced needs utilizing GENRAG's high-end RAG solution.

Intelligence Artificielle
Intelligence Artificielle, or Artificial Intelligence, refers to the use of AI technologies like RAG and ChatGPT to enhance information processing and decision-making in enterprises.

Retrieval-Augmented Generation
Retrieval-Augmented Generation is a workflow that combines information retrieval with text generation to provide precise, sourced answers within enterprises.

UI
UI, or User Interface, is part of GENRAG's offering, allowing customers to access and interact with RAG systems easily and efficiently.

API
API, or Application Programming Interface, is provided by GENRAG to facilitate interaction with and customization of its RAG systems.

Mistral 7B
Mistral 7B is a low-cost language model option available to Enterprise A as part of GENRAG's RAG solution package.

GPT-4O
GPT-4O is a high-end language model option provided to Enterprise B as part of GENRAG's advanced RAG solution offering.

2024 and 2034 AI Market Growth Projections
The global AI market is projected to grow from $638.23 billion in 2024 to $3,680.47 billion in 2034, highlighting a significant expansion over the next decade.

2025 and 2034 AI Market Growth Projections
An alternative market projection forecasts growth from $747.91 billion in 2025 to $3.68 trillion in 2034, showcasing a robust increase in AI adoption and innovation.

Flexible Subscription Model
GENRAG offers a flexible subscription model for its RAG services, adjusting costs based on resource usage and complexity of the implementation.

Julie Martin
Julie Martin is a 33-year-old technical project manager with 10 years of experience in IT project management, based in Bordeaux, France, working for a SaaS software company. She aims to quickly find technical information and help junior developers access documentation efficiently.<SEP>Julie Martin is an IT project manager who uses GenRAG to efficiently access technical documents.

Bordeaux, France
Bordeaux is a city in France where Julie Martin, a technical project manager, is based.<SEP>Bordeaux, France, is the location where Sophie Lemoine works and lives.

Société de logiciels SaaS
The SaaS software company where Julie Martin works, specializing in developing software solutions.

Paul Garnier
Paul Garnier is a 38-year-old individual mentioned in the text, likely involved in a professional capacity with GENRAG or its related activities.<SEP>Paul Garnier is a 38-year-old risk management consultant with 15 years of experience in compliance and auditing, based in Lyon, France, working with a national bank.<SEP>Paul Garnier is a risk management consultant who uses GenRAG to retrieve regulatory information for compliance purposes.

AI Models
AI Models are integral to GENRAG's platform, enabling the deployment of intelligent assistants and supporting scalability.

Cloud Providers
Cloud Providers are mentioned as key partners in GENRAG's ecosystem, supporting infrastructure and hosting solutions.

European Legislation on AI
European Legislation on AI refers to regulatory frameworks impacting the adoption of AI solutions in the market.

Security and Confidentiality
Security and Confidentiality are concerns related to AI deployment, reflecting the need for safeguarding data and privacy.

Cost of Innovation
Cost of Innovation refers to the financial investment required for developing and implementing new AI technologies and solutions.

Technical Team
The Technical Team at GENRAG is responsible for web development, DevOps, and AI model improvement, crucial to the platform's success.

GenRAG
GenRAG is a customizable RAG system that offers an interface for formulating questions and retrieving precise answers from documentation swiftly.<SEP>GenRAG is an organization focused on revolutionizing access to internal knowledge through artificial intelligence. The company is involved in deploying advanced AI systems and providing scalable solutions.<SEP>GenRAG is an organization focused on transforming access to internal knowledge through artificial intelligence, specifically using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems.

Lyon, France
Lyon, France, is the location where Paul Garnier is based.

Sophie Lemoine
Sophie Lemoine is a 35-year-old HR manager with 15 years of experience, working for a large industrial group with over 10,000 employees, based in Bordeaux, France.<SEP>Sophie Lemoine is the head of human resources who uses GenRAG to automate access to HR documentation.

Banque Nationale
Banque Nationale is a national bank with thousands of regulatory reports, where Paul Garnier ensures compliance with laws.

Grand Groupe Industriel
Grand Groupe Industriel is a large industrial group with over 10,000 employees where Sophie Lemoine works as an HR manager.

Next.js
Next.js is a framework for building web applications with features like Server-Side Rendering (SSR) and Static Site Generation (SSG), enhancing performance and SEO.

Nest.js
Nest.js is a TypeScript-based framework following a modular architecture, ideal for managing microservices such as users and configurations.

PostgreSQL
PostgreSQL is a powerful relational database management system known for its advanced data handling, indexing capabilities, and data integrity.<SEP>PostgreSQL is a powerful, open-source object-relational database system utilized in the Neon serverless database offering.

Docker
Docker is a containerization platform that encapsulates everything needed for an application to run, allowing for portable and scalable deployment.<SEP>Docker is a platform for containerization, allowing for portable deployment by encapsulating everything needed to run an application in a container.

Kubernetes
Kubernetes is a container orchestration system that automates deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.<SEP>Kubernetes is an orchestration platform that manages containerized applications across a cluster of machines, facilitating scalability and deployment.

Google Cloud Platform
Google Cloud Platform is a suite of cloud computing services that enables the deployment and operation of applications using Google's infrastructure.

Grafana
Grafana is a tool that visualizes data from Prometheus, creating interactive dashboards and alerting notifications.<SEP>Grafana is an open-source platform for monitoring and observability, providing powerful visualization capabilities.

Prometheus
Prometheus is a monitoring tool that collects and stores metrics from cloud-native applications like Kubernetes, offering powerful alerting capabilities.<SEP>Prometheus is an open-source monitoring and alerting toolkit, widely used for recording real-time metrics in a time-series database.

Helm
Helm is a package manager for Kubernetes, facilitating the management of Kubernetes applications.<SEP>Helm is a tool for managing Kubernetes applications, allowing for easy versioning and updating through the use of charts.

Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
Google Cloud Platform provides cloud services including Google's managed Kubernetes service and tools for building CI/CD pipelines.

Neon
Neon offers a managed and scalable PostgreSQL serverless database with automatic scaling and usage-based billing.

Pinecone
Pinecone is a vector database optimized for semantic search and efficient retrieval of relevant documents.

Python
Python is a programming language commonly used in artificial intelligence.

FastAPI
FastAPI is a web framework for building APIs with high performance and optimized features.

LangChain
LangChain is a framework for creating complex pipelines optimized for vector-based retrieval and guidance (RAG).

LightRAG
LightRAG combines vector indexing and graphs for optimized search capabilities, ideal for graph-based retrieval.

IES Deployment
IES Deployment refers to the organization or project responsible for selecting and integrating key technologies for efficient deployment.

Road-map
The Road-map outlines the different phases of development and deployment, from conception to advanced functionalities.

CI/CD pipelines
CI/CD pipelines provide a process framework for continual integration, delivery, and deployment in software development.

Vector RAG
Vector RAG refers to vector-retrieval and guidance systems using vector databases to enhance document search and retrieval.

Graph RAG
Graph RAG involves using graph-based systems along with vector indexing for better search and retrieval capabilities.

NestJS
NestJS is a framework for building scalable and efficient server-side applications, monitored by tools like Prometheus.

Ingestion, Tokenization, and Embedding
These are initial processes involved in handling documents, including the extraction and processing of information for further analysis.

Frontend & User Experience Development
This involves creating user interfaces and prototypes to enhance user interaction and visualize queries and responses.

Launch & Advanced Features
The phase involves deploying systems in production, acquiring clients, collecting feedback, and integrating new AI functionalities such as image analysis.

PoC Innovation
PoC Innovation is an organization associated with AI expert Valentin Peron, contributing to GenRAG's integration of technological advancements.<SEP>PoC Innovation is an organization where both Valentin Peron and Quentin Bolloré work as AI R&D Developer and Software R&D Developer, respectively.

Machine Learning and Deep Learning
These are fields of artificial intelligence focused on building algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data.

LLM (Large Language Model)
LLM refers to a machine learning model designed to understand and generate human language text, which Valentin Peron is experienced in developing.

IT Project Management
IT Project Management refers to the disciplined approach to managing technology projects, a field in which Julie Martin operates while using GenRAG.

Risk Management
Risk Management involves identifying, assessing, and prioritizing risks, a practice in which Paul Garnier engages while utilizing GenRAG.

Human Resources
Human Resources is a field focusing on the management of people within organizations, relevant to Sophie Lemoine's use of GenRAG for accessing HR documentation.

Regulatory Information
Regulatory Information entails the rules and guidelines businesses must follow, which Paul Garnier retrieves using GenRAG for compliance.

Compliance
Compliance involves adhering to laws and regulations, and is a key aspect of Paul Garnier's utilization of GenRAG.
